Package ca.openosp.openo.lab.ca.all.parsers

Class MEDITECHHandler

java.lang.Object
ca.openosp.openo.lab.ca.all.parsers.MEDITECHHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
MessageHandler
Direct Known Subclasses:
IHAPOIHandler
public class MEDITECHHandler extends Object implements MessageHandler
HL7 Message Handler class SPECIFICALLY for Meditech's Physician Office Interface (POI) The Meditech POI is used mainly with Ontario's Local Health Integration Network (LHIN) facilitates and with BC's Interior Health Authority.

Authored by Colcamex Resources Inc. Sponsored by Trimara Corp.

    • init

      public void init(String hl7Body) throws ca.uhn.hl7v2.HL7Exception
      Description copied from interface: MessageHandler
      Initialize the 'msg' object and any other global variables that may be needed.

      The 'msg' object should be initialized with the following code: Parser p = new PipeParser(); p.setValidationContext(new NoValidation()); msg = (ORU_R01) p.parse(hl7Body.replaceAll( "\n", "\r\n" )); - If you wish to validate the message please see the hapi documentation at 'http://hl7api.sourceforge.net/' - The replaceAll statement is necessary to ensure that the parser correctly reads the end of each line.

      Specified by:
      init in interface MessageHandler
      Throws:
      ca.uhn.hl7v2.HL7Exception

    • getOBXFinalResultCount

      public int getOBXFinalResultCount()
      Description copied from interface: MessageHandler
      Returns the number used to order labs with matching accession numbers.

      - Multiple labs with the same accession number must display in a certain order. They are ordered by their date but if two labs with the same accession number have the same date they are ordered by the number retrievied by this method

      - The newest lab will have the greatest number returned from this method.

      - If the hl7 messages do not contain a version number or other such number, the total number of obx segments with final results should be returned

      Specified by:
      getOBXFinalResultCount in interface MessageHandler
